The Sultan of Sokoto, His Eminence Muhammad Sa’ad Abubakar III Saturday requested Muslims to start looking for the new moon of Ramadan 1440A.H today. According to him, Sunday, May 5, which is equivalent to 29 day of Sha’aban 1440A.H. shall be the day to look for the new moon of Ramadan 1440A.H. This was contained in a statement signed by the Chairman, Advisory Committee on Religious Affairs, Sultanate Council, Sokoto, Professor Sambo Junaidu. He said they should report the sighting of the moon to the nearest district or village head for onward communication to the Sultan. The Sultan added that the general public can report the sighting of the new moon directly to the Sultan through the following phone numbers: 08037157100, 07067416900, 08066303077, 08065480405, 08035965322, 08036149757 and 08035945903. Also, the Nigerian Supreme Council for Islamic Affairs (NSCIA), under the leadership of the Sultan has urged the Muslims across the country to look out this year’s Ramadan after sunset on Sunday. The Deputy Secretary-General of the council, Professor Salisu Shehu, gave the advice on Saturday in a statement. According to him, consequent upon the advice of the National Moon Sighting Committee (NMSC), the President-General enjoins the Nigerian Muslim Ummah to search for the crescent of Ramadan 1440 AH immediately after sunset on Sunday. He also listed established and traditional Islamic leaders in each locality, members of the (NMSC) who can be contacted for information and clarification. They include Sheikh Dahir Bauchi 08036121311; Sheikh Karibullah Kabara 08035537382; Malam Simwal Usman Jibrin 08033140010; Sheikh Salihu Yaaqub, 07032558231; Malam Jafar Abubakar, 08020878075; Alhaji Abdullahi Umar 08037020607; Prof. J.M. Kaura 08067050641; Dr. Bashir Aliyu Umar, 08036509363; Sheikh Habeebullah Adam Al-Ilory, 08023126335; Malam Nurudeen Ibrahim 08027091623 and Sheikh  Abdur-Razzaq Ishola, 08023864448, 08051111063 among others. New moon expected Sunday to usher Ramadan R